<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sculptor Capital Management Inc. is a publicly=
 traded hedge fund firm that has agreed to sell itself to Rithm Capital Cor=
p., another investment manager, for $11.15 per share. Since Sculptor signed=
 the Rithm deal in July, another bidder has emerged: a group of mostly hedg=
e fund managers, led by Boaz Weinstein and including Marc Lasry and Bill Ac=
kman, who want to buy Sculptor with their personal funds, and who put in a =
bid earlier this month for $12.25. So far, though, Sculptor has said no: It=
s board of directors is sticking with the $11.15 Rithm deal rather than tak=
ing, or even really discussing, the $12.25 Weinstein deal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32571530.259423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
